com.poesys.db.dto

Class AbstractLazyListSetter<T extends IDbDto,P extends IDbDto,C extends java.util.Collection<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractSetter<T>
      • com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractListSetter<T,P,C>
        • com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractLazyListSetter<T,P,C>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of IDbDto to query
    P - the type of IDbDto that contains parameters for the query
    C - the Collection type of the set of DTOs to set into the object
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISet, java.io.Serializable

    public abstract class AbstractLazyListSetter<T extends IDbDto,P extends IDbDto,C extends java.util.Collection<T>>
extends AbstractListSetter<T,P,C>
    An abstract implementation of the ISet interface for a Strategy-pattern class that sets a list element of a data transfer object as a lazy-loading operation, taking in a connection and closing it. The abstract methods parameterize the class with objects that the set() method uses in processing the query.
    Author:
    Robert J. Muller
